paragraph.paragraph:
Eiffel provides syntax for expressing preconditions (

				require
			), postconditions (

				ensure
			) and class invariants (

				invariant
			), as well as other assertion constructs studied later (see 

				tutorial-11.xml38021
				Chapter 10, "Other Mechanisms"
			): loop invariants and variants, check instructions.

The words
interface class are used instead of just
class to avoid any confusion with actual Eiffel text, since this is documentation, not executable software. (It is in fact possible to generate a compilable variant of the Contract Form in the form of a deferred class, a notion defined later.)
